I feel like I should document my recovery, since people doing so helped me a lot.

I had surgery yesterday morning. I got wheeled back into the OR about 22ish hours ago.

I was worried about getting sleep last night. But that went really well. I'm basically just up early because I'm just like, excited. Lol

The pain in my inguinal canals is barely present now, even though that was the thing that was basically bugging me the most yesterday. Maybe it will come back again after I'm sitting up and moving around today.

I've only been taking Tylenol (acetaminophen/paracetamol) for pain since the hospital. They gave me tramadol but I doubt I'll need it.

Also, I've been hearing a lot about post-surgery nausea. I didn't have that problem almost at all. Just this lingering icky burp feeling occasionally during recovery at the hospital.

They offered me Ativan (Lorazepam) before surgery. I told them I heard anxiety meds increase recovery time, they said that wouldn't be an issue. Since I was starting to feel anxious I took it. It helped.

Also I guess I was intubated during surgery. That was kind of scary, but I don't remember the breathing tube at all. My throat was a bit irritated after surgery. It feels fine today.

This episode was fantastic.

1. I loved all the eastereggs that were not only Star Trek, but also the subtly not so subtle Star Wars/Mos Eisley reference on the Captain's mission to find Locarno: The hive of Scum and Villainy. And if you want to compare,

Tatooine Music and the Music played when the Cerritos Crew landed in the Shuttle, are very, very similar. LOVE that detail.

2. How we get all the abducted crews on that planet where Tendi, Boimler, T'Lyn, and Mariner go is very clever and so Star Trek. "Allegiance" from TNG comes to mind.

3. Getting more insight with Mariner's issues played so well with her fight/friendship situation with the Klingon Ma'ah we first met in the second Season wej Duj episode. There was a callback to B'Elana Torres (VOY: Exreme Risk) and her Trauma from the Dominion War.

4. T'Lyn being her amazing self again. I hope we get her on a much more regular basis.

5. The reveal for the mystery ship is sublime. Not what I ever expected, but so fitting with the themes and callbacks Lower Decks does.
